---
import { author } from "@data/constants/author"
---

<article
    class="about-paragraph"
    id="about-p"
    itemscope
    itemtype="http://schema.org/about"
>
    {/* META tags for SEO */}
    <meta itemprop="name" content={author.name}>
    <meta itemprop="author" content={author.name}>
    <meta itemprop="nationality" content="Brazilian">
    <meta itemprop="jobTitle" content={author.job}>
    <meta itemprop="image" content={`${import.meta.env.SITE}/favicon.svg`}>
    <meta itemprop="url" content={`${import.meta.env.SITE}/about`}>

    <strong itemprop="name">André Valério</strong> is a
    <strong itemprop="nationality" lang="en">Brazilian-born</strong>
    <strong itemprop="jobTitle">guitarist</strong>, 
    <strong itemprop="jobTitle">composer</strong>, 
    <strong itemprop="jobTitle">arranger</strong>, and 
    <strong itemprop="jobTitle">educator</strong> based in Toronto, celebrated for his 
    <strong itemprop="skills">versatility</strong>, 
    <strong itemprop="passion">passion for teaching</strong>, and deep connection to 
    <strong itemprop="genre">Brazilian music traditions</strong>.
    An in-demand performer on Canada’s 
    <strong itemprop="genre">world</strong> and 
    <strong itemprop="genre">jazz</strong> scenes, André is the 
    <slot name="div-1" />
    <strong itemprop="jobTitle">guitarist</strong> for 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="band">Tio Chorinho</strong>, Canada’s first ensemble dedicated to the traditional Brazilian style of 
    <strong itemprop="genre">choro</strong>. With the group, he won 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="award">Instrumental Ensemble of the Year</strong> at the 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="event">2024 Canadian Folk Music Awards</strong> for their acclaimed 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="album">album Tempestuoso</strong> — a vibrant collection of original and classic 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="genre">choros</strong> that showcases the ensemble’s dynamic energy and deep musicality.
    In addition to <span translate="no">Tio Chorinho</span>, André leads the 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="band">Ona Ensemble</strong>, a Canadian-Brazilian 
    <strong itemprop="genre">chamber jazz group</strong> known for its inventive arrangements and cultural fusion. The group recently completed a successful 
    <strong itemprop="event">tour in Brazil</strong>, where they recorded an 
    <strong itemprop="album">EP</strong> featuring the legendary 
    <strong itemprop="musicalArtist">composer and guitarist <span >Filó Machado</span></strong>.
    A prolific <strong itemprop="jobTitle">composer</strong> and 
    <strong itemprop="jobTitle">arranger</strong>, André has collaborated extensively with 
    <strong itemprop="musicalArtist">vocalists</strong> such as 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="musicalArtist">Kalya Ramu</strong>, 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="musicalArtist">Flávia Nascimento</strong>, and 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="musicalArtist">Carlos Cardozo</strong>, contributing original 
    <strong itemprop="workPerformed">songs</strong> and 
    <strong itemprop="workPerformed">arrangements</strong> that reflect his melodic sensibility and love for storytelling through music.
    <slot name="div-2" />
    As an <strong itemprop="jobTitle">educator</strong>, André is a dedicated teacher who inspires students of all levels. With years of experience teaching 
    <strong itemprop="teaches">guitar</strong>, 
    <strong itemprop="teaches">harmony</strong>, and 
    <strong itemprop="teaches">improvisation</strong> — both in person and online — he is known for his patient, intuitive, and encouraging approach. His students benefit not only from his deep 
    <strong itemprop="skills">knowledge</strong> but also from his genuine joy in sharing music.
    Whether performing on stage, composing in the studio, or guiding a student through a new piece, 
    <strong translate="no" itemprop="name">André Valério</strong> brings heart, clarity, and artistry to everything he does.
</article>




<style lang="scss" is:global >
$mark_quantity: 45; // Number of <strong> elements to animate
$color: var(--secondary-color, black);

@keyframes highlight {
    0% {
        background-position: 100%;
    }
    100% {
        background-position: 0%;
    }
}

.about-paragraph#about-p {
    strong {
        background: linear-gradient(
            to right,
            $color 50%,
            oklch(0.86 0.19 84.89 / 0) 50%
        );
        background-position: 100%;
        background-size: 200% 100%;
        border-radius: 0.125rem;
        padding-inline: 0.125rem;
        animation: none;
    
        .visible & {
            animation: highlight .5s linear forwards;
        }
    }
}

@for $i from 1 through $mark_quantity {
    .about-paragraph#about-p strong:nth-child(#{$i}) {
        animation-delay: #{200ms * $i};
    }
}
  
</style>